title: Week One Blog
text:
Week One Highlights
In week one, I first made sure all my github and datacamp accounts were in order. However, due to some issues with datacamp, did not get a head start on training.
Day 1: Did k-means clustering and statistical analysis on the flight data of scheduled flights and actual flights in 90-minute data science exercise. Presented findings to the whole DSPG team.




Day 2: Went through past DSPG projects.
Day 3: Met with Courtney Long to discuss project expectations, fixed DataCamp access issues by meeting Rakesh and Chris

title: Week Three Blog
text:
Week Three Highlights
We had a long weekend so Monday was a change than usual, and I got to sleep in!
Tuesday and Wednesday- I was out of office due to health reasons
Thursday- Worked on collecting data from Iowa Grocers excel file for prices on eggs, bacon and heirloom tomatoes. Finished cities in Iowa starting from the letter C and finished that. Proceeded to work on cities from letter I. Completed cities from O to R and W as well.
Finished Datacamp Web Scraping Course.
